commit_message: Dropped direct dependency on 'PyVCF' -- it's hanled by 'SNPy' now

Added more logging to 'naive_lookup'
Added minimal 'logging' and UNIX-only file locking on 'Genome.dump()'
Turns out median is 'too much', switched to 25th percentile
Fixed cutoff formula, damn those iterators!
Fixed 'shortopt' values for 'index' and 'partial' commands
Switched to median for calculating the cutoff in 'naive_lookup'
Okay, officially renamed to 'consequnce' ;)

Updated 'README.md'

  We don't need any aditional maps for partial reference
Added a draft version of partial reference builder
Added 'requirements.txt'
Added a one-liner fix for 'pysam' indexing

Removed position converting nonsense (*sigh*) and updated score calculation

  SNP score is now defined as 'sum(mapq-values) / position-base-coverage'

Fixed a bug in 'Genome.load'

  Nothing was loaded, when chrom. list wasn't given explicitly

Turns out VCF contains positions relative to *chromosome* start

  So now, 'update_index' first calculates offsets for each chromosome
  in the reference sequence and afters adds VCF items to the
  index, converting relative positions to genome-wide
Merged '*_index' methods into 'load' and 'dump'

Wrong again 'AlignedRead.tid' attribute is just an internal identifier

Finally -- picked the insert size, used for partial reference
